                          Profession Inlays

    Profession-crafted gear can be improved after it is made by adding a
saved shard as an inlay. Inlays are done in the profession building, 4e, n
from Center of Town.

Command:
  inlay <crafted item> with <shard>

Example:
  inlay breastplate with mithril
  inlay robe with amber

    Inlaying consumes one saved shard from your reagent/material storage and
adds a small stat or resistance bonus to a profession-crafted item. Each item
can only hold one profession inlay.

    The item must be profession-crafted gear. Ordinary loot, quest gear, and
items that already have a profession inlay cannot be inlaid again.

    Shards can come from profession work orders and other profession systems.
Use 'reagents' to check the shards you have saved, and
'reagents search <shard>' to look for source hints.

    Metal, leather, and gem shards grant different bonuses. Smithing,
leatherworking, and tailoring help files list the common material and shard
bonus themes used by profession-crafted gear.

